                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/2022: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Crane</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-04-13T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 13, 1921—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>115. Your 141, April 4, 4 p.m.</p>
                <p>Department has been endeavoring through negotiations with Prague and Paris to
                    secure for the Chinese Eastern payment of Czech transportation bill. Czechs
                    state at present they have no money to pay. French are reluctant to admit
                    responsibility for Czech transportation but matter is not yet considered
                    hopeless. It would not in any case be possible for the United States to give
                    consideration to the question of furnishing funds to meet this obligation
                    pending a satisfactory adjustment of the question of railway control.</p>
                <p>Advise Colonel Johnson for Technical Board’s information.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
